'''Matt Doran''' (born [[March 30]], [[1976]] in [[Wikipedia:Sydney|Sydney]], [[Wikipedia:New South Wales|New South Wales]]) is an [[Wikipedia:Australians|Australian]] actor. In [[2002]], he played [[death stick]] dealer [[Elan Sel'Sabagno|Elan Sleazebaggano]] in {{Film|II}}.

Doran also played "Mouse" in [[1999]]'s ''[[Wikipedia:The Matrix|The Matrix]]'', and is known in [[Wikipedia:Australia|Australia]] for playing the character of [[Wikipedia:Damian Roberts|Damian Roberts]] on the soap opera ''[[Wikipedia:Home and Away|Home and Away]]''.

